<p pid="41">In a modern development workflow, both command-line and a graphical user interface has its place. On the GUI side, Eclipse is famous and offers many different ways to accomplish something that is great. But sometimes, I continue to use an old habit or way because I have missed that there is a newer and better way, and the MCUXpresso Eclipse IDE is no exception to that. In this article, I show a few ways how to use the mouse even more productive.</p>
